<input type="hidden" name="mailcatcher[install]" value="0" />

<div class="section-header">
    <h1>MailCatcher</h1>
    <p class="lead">Install MailCatcher.</p>
</div>

<div class="field-container">
    <div class="form-group">
        <label class="col-xs-12 radio-tile">
            <input type="checkbox" name="mailcatcher[install]" value="1"
                   class="invisible toggle-on-select"
                   {% if mailcatcher.install %}checked{% endif %}
                   data-vis-toggle-target="#mailcatcher-container" />
            <span class="content">
                <span class="header large">
                    <i class="icon"></i>
                    <span class="title">Install MailCatcher</span>
                </span>
                <span class="footer">
                    Catches mail and serves it through a dream.
                </span>
            </span>
        </label>

        <div class="clearfix"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="clearfix"></div>

    <div id="mailcatcher-container" class="{% if not mailcatcher.install %}hidden{% endif %}">
        <div class="form-group col-xs-6">
            <div class="help-text">
                <p>MailCatcher will be available at
                    <code>http://{SERVER_IP_ADDRESS}:{HTTP_PORT}</code></p>
                <p>It is highly recommended <strong>not</strong> installing
                    Mailcatcher on production servers.</p>
                <p>Minimum port number is <code>1000</code>.</p>
            </div>
            <label for="mailcatcher-settings-http_port">HTTP Port</label>
            <input type="number" id="mailcatcher-settings-http_port"
                   name="mailcatcher[settings][http_port]"
                   placeholder="1080" class="form-control"
                   value="{{ mailcatcher.settings.http_port }}" />
        </div>

        <div class="form-group col-xs-6">
            <div class="clearfix"><label>From Address Method</label></div>

            <label class="radio-tile mini set-width">
                <input type="radio" class="invisible"
                       name="mailcatcher[settings][from_email_method]"
                       value="inline"
                       {% if mailcatcher.settings.from_email_method == 'inline' %}checked{% endif %} />
                <span class="content">
                    <span class="header">
                        <i class="icon"></i>
                        <span class="title">Inline</span>
                    </span>
                </span>
            </label>

            <label class="radio-tile mini set-width">
                <input type="radio" class="invisible"
                       name="mailcatcher[settings][from_email_method]"
                       value="headers"
                       {% if mailcatcher.settings.from_email_method == 'headers' %}checked{% endif %} />
                <span class="content">
                    <span class="header">
                        <i class="icon"></i>
                        <span class="title">Headers</span>
                    </span>
                </span>
            </label>
        </div>

        <div class="clearfix"></div>

        <div class="help-block">
            <p><a href="https://github.com/puphpet/puphpet/issues/932#issuecomment-51086541"
               target="_blank">Per this issue</a>
                Mailcatcher seems to have a bug where you can define your email's
                <strong>from</strong> value either inline in your code, or as header values.</p>
            <p>If you send email like
                <code>mail('to@email.com', 'the subject', 'the message', null, 'from@email.com');</code>
                then choose <code>Inline</code> above. Otherwise, choose <code>Headers</code>.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="clearfix"></div>

    <div class="col-xs-6">
        <a class="btn btn-lg btn-success btn-block next-section" type="button" href="#sqlite">
            <i class="fa fa-hand-o-left"></i> SQLite
        </a>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-6">
        <a class="btn btn-lg btn-success btn-block next-section" type="button" href="#beanstalkd">
            Beanstalkd <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"></i>
        </a>
    </div>

    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>
